Package Services.Response

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClearResponse
    A class that holds the response message for the clear service Inherits from Response Fields: message and an error flag
    EResponse
    A class that is a string representation of an event, used in eventResponse
    EventResponse
    Contains information used in the response of event Fields: error flag, message, and a list of events
    FillResponse
    A class that represents the response message of the fill service Inherits from the Response class
    LoadResponse
    A class that holds the information needed for a load result Fields: usersAdded, eventsAdded, personsAdded, error flag and a message
    LoginResponse
    A class that contains all of the information that the login service returns Inherits from the response class Fields: userName, id
    PersonResponse
    A class that contains an array of PResponse objects, which represent persons in the database
    PResponse
    A class that contains all the information representing a person in the database Not meant to be directly instantiated.
    RegisterResponse
    A class that holds all of the information for a register result Fields: userName, id, and an AuthToken
    Response
    A response superclass.
